e-with-cranfield-create-uks-second-largest-university/articleshow/131090869.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/kings-college-london-to-merge-with-cranfield-create-uks-second-largest-university/articleshow/131090869.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-14T16:46:54+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131091397,imgsize-1131275.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[UAE among world’s fastest-growing billionaire hubs with 17 residents worth $212.6 billion: Forbes]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131090746.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Indian-origin billionaires are increasingly powering the UAE's wealth, with nine individuals on Forbes Middle East's 2026 list commanding $49.9 billion. These entrepreneurs have built multi-billion-dollar businesses across various sectors, reflecting the UAE's appeal as a hub for global wealth due to its business-friendly policies and strategic location.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/uae-among-worlds-fastest-growing-billionaire-hubs-with-17-residents-worth-212-6-billion-forbes/articleshow/131090746.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/uae-among-worlds-fastest-growing-billionaire-hubs-with-17-residents-worth-212-6-billion-forbes/articleshow/131090746.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-14T16:43:07+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131091281,imgsize-179260.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Xi exception: Why we saw a toned-down Trump in China]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131090475.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[During a Beijing visit, President Trump observed China's military might, signaling a shift in global power. While the US faces munitions shortages and slow production, China's defense industry operates at wartime pace, excelling in drones, AI, and satellite tech. This evolving warfare, particularly concerning Taiwan, highlights a contest for future global dominance.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/defence/international/the-xi-exception-why-we-saw-a-toned-down-trump-in-china/articleshow/131090475.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/defence/international/the-xi-exception-why-we-saw-a-toned-down-trump-in-china/articleshow/131090475.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-14T16:35:33+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Abhishek Mishra</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131090404,imgsize-1481845.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[UK launches world-first roadside ‘laughing gas’ breath test in southern England: New device targets growing drug-driving crisis on roads]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131088205.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/uk-launches-world-first-roadside-laughing-gas-breath-test-in-southern-england-new-device-targets-growing-drug-driving-crisis-on-roads/articleshow/131088205.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/uk-launches-world-first-roadside-laughing-gas-breath-test-in-southern-england-new-device-targets-growing-drug-driving-crisis-on-roads/articleshow/131088205.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-14T16:20:32+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131090724,imgsize-84252.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[In 1913, Harry Brearley accidentally created stainless steel while testing rifle barrels]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131064811.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Sheffield metallurgist Harry Brearley's accidental 1913 discovery of corrosion-resistant steel, while seeking solutions for rifle barrel wear, revolutionized manufacturing. This practical, factory-floor innovation, born from routine testing, proved crucial for industries needing durable, hygienic materials. Stainless steel's enduring relevance highlights how addressing practical problems can lead to globally impactful, long-lasting inventions.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/in-1913-harry-brearley-accidentally-created-stainless-steel-while-testing-rifle-barrels/articleshow/131064811.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/in-1913-harry-brearley-accidentally-created-stainless-steel-while-testing-rifle-barrels/articleshow/131064811.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-14T16:15:20+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131064828,imgsize-17682.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[In 1941, George de Mestral got annoyed by sticky burrs on his dog, and this accidentally launched the multibillion-dollar Velcro industry]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131064407.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Swiss engineer Georges de Mestral observed burrs attaching to his dog's fur, leading to the invention of Velcro. He discovered the burrs' hook-and-loop mechanism, which inspired a durable, reattachable fastener. NASA's adoption of Velcro for space missions further popularized this biomimicry innovation, showcasing nature's engineering solutions.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/in-1941-george-de-mestral-got-annoyed-by-sticky-burrs-on-his-dog-and-this-accidentally-launched-the-multibillion-dollar-velcro-industry/articleshow/131064407.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/in-1941-george-de-mestral-got-annoyed-by-sticky-burrs-on-his-dog-and-this-accidentally-launched-the-multibillion-dollar-velcro-industry/articleshow/131064407.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-14T16:12:19+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131064356,imgsize-201240.cms"/></item></channel></rss>